WEBVTT

00:01.373 --> 00:02.352
There are two kinds of folks

00:02.379 --> 00:03.979
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:04.313 --> 00:06.039
Psychopaths and mystery writers.

00:06.277 --> 00:07.299
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:07.700 --> 00:08.300
Who am I?

00:08.389 --> 00:09.528
I'm Rick Castle.

00:09.529 --> 00:09.929
Castle.

00:09.963 --> 00:10.623
Castle.

00:10.624 --> 00:12.624
I really am ruggedly
handsome, aren't I?

00:12.770 --> 00:14.960
Every writer needs inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:15.170 --> 00:15.989
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:16.024 --> 00:17.044
- Beckett.
- Beckett.

00:17.079 --> 00:18.985
- Nikki Heat?
- The character he's basing on you.

00:19.031 --> 00:20.517
And thanks to my
friendship with the mayor,

00:20.518 --> 00:21.518
I get to be on her case.

00:21.552 --> 00:23.495
I would be happy to
let you spank me.

00:23.530 --> 00:24.406
And together, we catch killers

00:25.354 --> 00:26.342
we make a pretty good team,
you know?

00:26.343 --> 00:27.343
Like Starsky and Hutch.

00:27.477 --> 00:28.171
Turner and Hooch.

00:28.534 --> 00:29.601
You do remind me a little of Hooch.

00:31.000 --> 00:37.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:45.528 --> 00:47.145
This is Blackbird. Identification.

00:47.265 --> 00:49.728
Designate 2-2-3.
I am blown. I am blown.

00:49.977 --> 00:51.614
This call is unauthorized, 2-2-3.

00:51.615 --> 00:53.819
This line is not secure.
Where is the safe house?

00:53.820 --> 00:56.091
Negative, 2-2-3.
You know the rules.

01:21.550 --> 01:23.882
<i>We've got something between us</i>
<i>nothing can change.</i>

01:23.883 --> 01:26.825
<i>Oh, well, I suppose you're right in a way,
Walter.</i>

01:26.945 --> 01:28.619
<i>Sure, I'm right... Aren't you
gonna answer that?</i>

01:28.739 --> 01:29.739
Nope.

01:29.859 --> 01:31.572
Oh-- and neither are you.

01:31.692 --> 01:34.142
Ahh. Who are you hiding from now?

01:34.397 --> 01:36.189
Gina.

01:36.309 --> 01:38.141
Ohh. Forget an alimony payment?

01:38.385 --> 01:40.071
No, this time she's not
calling as my ex-wife.

01:40.072 --> 01:41.487
She's calling as my publisher.

01:41.607 --> 01:44.110
The first draft of my new
manuscript was due yesterday,

01:44.111 --> 01:45.526
and I haven't finished.

01:45.646 --> 01:47.580
Why not? Haven't felt like writing.

01:47.700 --> 01:49.274
And besides, I don't
think I'm entirely happy

01:49.394 --> 01:51.011
with where my characters are going.

01:51.284 --> 01:53.351
Well... change them.

01:54.125 --> 01:56.063
Working on it.
What are you doing here?

01:56.183 --> 01:57.685
I thought you had an audition
for williamstown tonight.

01:57.805 --> 01:59.904
I do. Just came to pick
up my lucky blouse.

02:00.024 --> 02:01.971
Aah! I got in! I got in!

02:02.091 --> 02:03.248
Oh, good.

02:03.368 --> 02:05.688
Oh, my God. You got in.
That's amazing! I can't b--

02:05.808 --> 02:07.095
I don't--what-
what did you get into?

02:07.215 --> 02:09.122
Princeton's summer program
for High School students.

02:09.495 --> 02:11.216
I thought you got wait-listed.
Someone just canceled,

02:11.217 --> 02:12.911
but we have to send
them a deposit A.S.A.P.,

02:13.031 --> 02:15.496
because it starts this weekend.
This weekend?

02:15.812 --> 02:17.938
I know we had plans,
but-- not just plans--

02:18.058 --> 02:20.245
Memorial Day, the Hamptons,

02:20.365 --> 02:22.266
our annual "kick off
the summer" week.

02:22.386 --> 02:24.534
I mean, I got the
illegal fireworks,

02:24.535 --> 02:26.855
the kind you like, the ones
with the silver starbursts.

02:27.185 --> 02:28.588
Dad, it's Princeton.

02:28.708 --> 02:30.345
I can't believe you would
blow off illegal fireworks

02:30.465 --> 02:32.269
for a lousy head start
at a top-notch education.

02:32.389 --> 02:33.906
I know. I'm a huge disappointment.

02:34.280 --> 02:35.825
Now there are a bunch of
forms you need to sign,

02:35.945 --> 02:37.029
and I'll fill the rest
out for you later.

02:37.149 --> 02:39.151
Mm-hmm. Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey.

02:40.070 --> 02:42.065
It says here that the,
uh, the dorms are coed.

02:42.307 --> 02:44.860
Yeah, it's college. No.

02:44.861 --> 02:47.563
No, it's a summer program
for High School students

02:47.564 --> 02:49.066
<i>at</i> a college.

02:49.067 --> 02:51.372
According to this,
half the kids in your building

02:51.492 --> 02:53.057
will be 16- and 17-year-old boys.

02:53.177 --> 02:56.474
<i>Relax,</i> dad. Each floor has a
resident advisor who's 21.

02:57.045 --> 02:58.946
Oh, so the one person in charge

02:58.947 --> 03:00.916
is conveniently old
enough to buy alcohol?

03:01.036 --> 03:02.971
Darling, don't be such a prude.

03:03.215 --> 03:05.564
Remember that trip you took
to Italy with your class?

03:05.684 --> 03:07.322
You were younger
than Alexis is now.

03:07.442 --> 03:10.165
Mother, if you had any idea
what happened on that trip,

03:10.285 --> 03:12.491
you would've never let
me leave the house again.

03:13.578 --> 03:16.158
Sometimes, the less you know,
the better.

03:18.562 --> 03:20.263
Ah.

03:21.499 --> 03:22.684
Beckett.

03:22.804 --> 03:24.227
You have a novel to finish.

03:24.347 --> 03:25.417
Mnh-mnh-mnh.

03:25.537 --> 03:27.037
It's Castle.

03:28.511 --> 03:29.803
It's kinda like a tradition--

03:29.923 --> 03:32.177
you know, bonfires,
roasting marshmallows,

03:32.178 --> 03:33.812
telling ghost stories,
sleeping late.

03:34.128 --> 03:35.757
We've done it since she was 5.

03:36.231 --> 03:38.768
Sounds nice.
Kinda magical, actually.

03:39.153 --> 03:41.087
Yeah, you know what?
You should come.

03:41.088 --> 03:43.138
Oh, it's right on the ocean.
There's a secluded pool.

03:43.258 --> 03:44.920
You could lay out,
work on your tan.

03:45.308 --> 03:47.271
Wow, Castle,
you're working really hard

03:47.391 --> 03:48.913
to see me in a swimsuit.

03:49.033 --> 03:50.746
If you are not comfortable
in a swimsuit,

03:50.866 --> 03:53.701
you can just skinny-dip.

03:53.702 --> 03:55.186
The vic's a white male,

03:55.306 --> 03:57.159
multiple gunshot
wounds to the chest.

03:57.461 --> 03:58.906
Found him about an hour ago.

03:59.026 --> 04:00.089
Mugging?

04:00.209 --> 04:02.481
Nah. He still has his watch,
wallet and cash.

04:02.601 --> 04:04.703
Then there's the matter
of the phantom bullets.

04:04.823 --> 04:06.297
Yeah, he took five to the chest.

04:06.670 --> 04:08.125
There are no slugs, Shell casings.

04:08.245 --> 04:10.841
The killer went so far as to dig his bullets
out of that tree branch right there.

04:10.961 --> 04:12.989
That's weird.
What about in the body?

04:12.990 --> 04:14.313
They're all through and throughs.

04:14.433 --> 04:15.909
Exit holes on each wound.

04:16.029 --> 04:18.243
So our doer cleaned
up after himself.

04:18.363 --> 04:20.262
It takes <i>real</i> presence of mind

04:20.264 --> 04:22.199
to put five bullets
into a man's chest

04:22.200 --> 04:23.730
and then keep your cool long enough

04:23.850 --> 04:26.816
to pick up after yourself.
Natural instinct is to run.

04:27.172 --> 04:29.218
I would say we are most
likely dealing with

04:29.490 --> 04:30.845
a highly trained assassin.

04:31.873 --> 04:32.878
Time of death?

04:32.998 --> 04:34.419
Based on temperature and lividity,

04:34.539 --> 04:36.942
I'd say between 11:00 P.
M. and 1:00 A.M.

04:37.062 --> 04:37.963
I.D.?

04:38.083 --> 04:40.285
Shawn Caldwell.
No driver's license,

04:40.405 --> 04:42.047
but according to his work I.D.,

04:42.291 --> 04:44.448
he was a consultant for F.
G.S. In Midtown.

04:44.692 --> 04:46.467
"Fastwater Global Services"?

04:46.587 --> 04:48.074
Sounds like a CIA front.

04:48.677 --> 04:49.918
Found these in his pocket.

04:50.842 --> 04:52.163
Company car keys.

04:52.283 --> 04:53.983
There's no house keys on the chain.

04:55.213 --> 04:57.538
There's a generic hotel key card.

04:57.658 --> 04:59.910
In from out of town?
Except the company address is local,

05:00.498 --> 05:02.021
and so is his gym membership.
All right.

05:02.141 --> 05:04.177
Have C.S.U. Sweep the area,
canvass the homeless people,

05:04.297 --> 05:06.369
see if anyone saw
or heard anything.

05:19.878 --> 05:22.080
Ocean view from my patio.

05:22.081 --> 05:24.683
It <i>does not</i> get better than this.

05:26.185 --> 05:28.888
What's wrong? I tried
information, our database.

05:28.889 --> 05:30.857
I even did an Internet search,

05:30.858 --> 05:32.072
and it's like these
guys don't even exist.

05:32.192 --> 05:34.120
Who? Fastwater global services.

05:34.240 --> 05:36.262
Ah! See? I told you. CIA cover.

05:37.296 --> 05:39.126
No. I mean, they probably
just don't like to advertise.

05:39.246 --> 05:40.840
Yeah, well, I thought so as well,

05:40.960 --> 05:44.035
so I checked their address-
1747 West 43rd Street.

05:44.699 --> 05:46.468
It's in the middle
of the Hudson River.

05:47.364 --> 05:49.848
So I went back and checked
through his wallet

05:49.968 --> 05:51.780
and looked at his I.D.
S, his gym membership,

05:51.900 --> 05:53.883
health insurance,
even his atm card--

05:54.264 --> 05:56.345
they're all fakes.
You run his name?

05:56.790 --> 05:58.842
Yeah, there's about half
a dozen Shawn Caldwells

05:58.843 --> 06:00.505
in the tristate area,
and none of them are a match.

06:00.864 --> 06:02.958
What about his fingerprints?
Not in our system.

06:03.618 --> 06:05.495
Hey, Beckett. Hey, what'd you find?

06:05.615 --> 06:07.551
Well, we spoke to some
homeless guys who were camped

06:07.671 --> 06:09.124
a couple hundred yards from
the overpass last night.

06:09.244 --> 06:10.919
They didn't see or hear anything.

06:11.039 --> 06:13.316
Couple hundred yards?
How do you not hear five gunshots?

06:13.436 --> 06:15.319
Unless... He used a silencer.

06:15.439 --> 06:17.526
To kill a man who went out of
the way to hide who he was?

06:17.646 --> 06:19.965
This is starting to sound more
and more like a professional hit.

06:20.085 --> 06:21.354
Yeah, well, we're nowhere
until we figure out

06:21.474 --> 06:22.368
who this guy actually is.

06:22.488 --> 06:23.885
Why don't you guys
go canvass the area

06:24.005 --> 06:26.083
near the entrance to the park,
see if you can find his car?

06:26.428 --> 06:28.305
And fax his photo
to the local hotels,

06:28.425 --> 06:31.395
see if anyone recognizes
his face. Right on.

06:33.941 --> 06:35.554
You know, I-I was...

06:35.674 --> 06:37.334
I was kidding about
the assassin stuff.

06:40.077 --> 06:41.692
That's Lanie.

06:42.109 --> 06:43.803
Please tell me that
you found something.

06:43.923 --> 06:45.826
Well, I found nothing
that sheds light

06:45.946 --> 06:47.178
on the identity of your victim,

06:47.298 --> 06:49.398
but I did find something that
may help with your killer.

06:49.518 --> 06:51.716
We know the shooter tried
to scrub the crime scene

06:51.836 --> 06:53.747
of ballistic evidence,
but one of the rounds

06:53.867 --> 06:56.906
shattered Mr. Caldwell's rib
and left this little souvenir.

06:58.973 --> 07:00.988
A bullet fragment?
Can't tell the caliber,

07:01.108 --> 07:03.018
but this polygonal rifling
along the outer rim

07:03.138 --> 07:05.403
is consistent with the
barrel of a glock. Hmm.

07:05.647 --> 07:08.335
What? The grouping of the shots.

07:08.336 --> 07:10.372
You see how tight they all are?

07:10.373 --> 07:12.842
There's no stippling,
no muzzle burns.

07:13.127 --> 07:15.077
The killer must have
shot from a distance.

07:15.078 --> 07:17.078
Which means he's a very good shot.

07:18.647 --> 07:21.115
Hi.

07:21.116 --> 07:23.089
Great. Thanks.

07:23.548 --> 07:25.185
They found the car.

07:25.186 --> 07:27.020
Car is registered to
Allied Fleet Services,

07:27.021 --> 07:28.488
a car rental agency.

07:28.489 --> 07:30.485
Oh, I hope they got
the insurance option.

07:30.605 --> 07:31.921
Who did they rent it to?

07:32.041 --> 07:35.039
This particular car is on a
long-term lease to F.G.S.

07:35.682 --> 07:37.419
Fastwater Global Services.

07:37.539 --> 07:39.749
Do they know they rented their car
to a company that doesn't exist?

07:39.869 --> 07:41.707
Oh, no. It exists,
just not in New York.

07:41.827 --> 07:43.780
All correspondence,
billing and payments go through

07:43.900 --> 07:46.306
a P.O. Box in the Cayman Islands.
It gets even weirder.

07:46.426 --> 07:48.196
In the trunk, we found these.

07:49.446 --> 07:50.674
Euros.

07:50.675 --> 07:52.228
5,000 of 'em, and...

07:56.246 --> 07:57.998
That looks military. Yeah.

07:58.118 --> 07:59.793
What's in the box?

07:59.913 --> 08:01.916
A fancy pen. Nice!

08:02.036 --> 08:03.931
A bag full of Euros,
a high-tech heater

08:04.051 --> 08:06.101
and a silent killer
who leaves no trace...

08:06.221 --> 08:08.741
<i>Good evening, 2-2-3. Informant has
been identified.</i>

08:08.861 --> 08:11.679
<i>Ally contact will meet you at Café Moulin,
1315 hours... I didn't--I
didn't--</i>

08:11.799 --> 08:14.793
no, no, shh. <i>With further instructions.
Wear the pin and use</i>

08:14.794 --> 08:16.862
<i>the following code phrase-
</i> <i>"Aren't you Steve's friend?"</i>

08:16.982 --> 08:20.796
<i>Response, "no, Steve is my brother.
" Good luck, 2-2-3.</i>

08:20.797 --> 08:22.298
Whoa!

08:22.299 --> 08:24.898
Yeow. Ow!

08:24.899 --> 08:26.993
Well, now we know why our
victim doesn't exist.

08:27.911 --> 08:30.222
He's a spy.

08:31.570 --> 08:34.477
<font color=#7fff00>♪ Castle 2x24 ♪</font>
